00:36:51.904 --> 00:36:55.444
understood that breast cancer truly is different, we want to be able to study

652
00:36:55.504 --> 00:36:59.364
mechanistically what's happening, and how we might test

653
00:36:59.424 --> 00:37:01.464
response to therapy given different age.

654
00:37:01.494 --> 00:37:04.304
And to do that, we had to build some models in the laboratory.

655
00:37:04.944 --> 00:37:08.764
This is our overall workflow. As I mentioned, we have now

656
00:37:08.924 --> 00:37:11.804
a number of clinical studies that are focusing on older women.

657
00:37:12.284 --> 00:37:15.854
So we have tissues from younger and older patients that we're

658
00:37:15.964 --> 00:37:19.364
biobanking, blood, tumor tissue, that we

659
00:37:19.384 --> 00:37:23.274
do analyses, immunoprofiling, spatial analyses,

660
00:37:23.404 --> 00:37:26.784
generate data sets, or use publicly available data sets.

661
00:37:27.084 --> 00:37:30.944
And we couple that type of work with a lot of preclinical modeling

662
00:37:31.344 --> 00:37:34.904
using younger and older animals, testing various

663
00:37:35.044 --> 00:37:38.704
aspects of those interactions, cell-cell interactions, and functional

