1081
01:01:54.404 --> 01:01:58.034
right now, where we're trying to overcome what we think are aging-driven

1082
01:01:58.114 --> 01:02:00.884
barriers to effective immunotherapy in pancreatic

1083
01:02:00.884 --> 01:02:03.554
cancer. These are my disclosures.

1084
01:02:03.634 --> 01:02:07.554
And this is not surprising. Pancreatic cancer has not joined

1085
01:02:07.594 --> 01:02:11.414
the immunotherapy revolution. This is a very ICI-resistant tumor

1086
01:02:11.474 --> 01:02:11.794
type.

1087
01:02:12.934 --> 01:02:16.834
The lack of durable responses are there, even if you have the rare

1088
01:02:16.914 --> 01:02:20.824
patient who happens to respond by some chance to ICIs and

1089
01:02:20.894 --> 01:02:24.574
pancreatic cancer. And we're really lacking tumors that have these

1090
01:02:24.614 --> 01:02:25.654
exceptional responder

1091
01:02:26.494 --> 01:02:30.054
biomarkers. So there's not a lot of MSI-high, not a lot of

1092
01:02:30.154 --> 01:02:33.474
TMB-high tumors here. And you can see that they've done the trials.

1093
01:02:33.574 --> 01:02:36.394
These don't work. We don't use them in routine clinical practice.

1094
01:02:36.874 --> 01:02:40.254
And I think a lot of us are trying to figure out how can we leverage some more

1095
01:02:40.294 --> 01:02:44.274
