1096
01:02:44.294 --> 01:02:46.554
responses we're hoping for our patients.

1097
01:02:47.694 --> 01:02:50.514
Now, the TME that I just mentioned in pancreas cancer is

1098
01:02:51.514 --> 01:02:55.484
a very hostile environment for an effective anti-tumor immune response.

1099
01:02:55.914 --> 01:02:59.374
There's a lot of complex interactions between cancer cells and

1100
01:02:59.394 --> 01:03:03.364
non-malignant cells. This includes a lot of fibroblasts that are making

1101
01:03:03.374 --> 01:03:06.614
up the bulk of a tumor in PDACs. It's very

1102
01:03:06.654 --> 01:03:10.324
desmoplastic and often immune excluded, so just not

1103
01:03:10.354 --> 01:03:11.854
many effector immune cells there.

1104
01:03:12.014 --> 01:03:15.614
Not just ones that are exhausted, they're just not there to be found.

1105
01:03:15.634 --> 01:03:18.734
This really hinders effective immune responses in this disease.

1106
01:03:19.494 --> 01:03:23.374
And despite a lot of great studies of the TME and pancreas cancer,

1107
01:03:23.494 --> 01:03:27.034
we've not done a great job of translating the findings from pre-clinical

1108
01:03:27.094 --> 01:03:30.854
models into new therapies or new treatment approaches for patients.

1109
01:03:31.594 --> 01:03:35.334
We've tried some approaches to target desmoplasia itself and the

1110
01:03:35.374 --> 01:03:38.754
CAFs, and we're still trying to scratch our heads and figure out how do we move

1111
01:03:38.764 --> 01:03:42.514
this from mice into humans and get those

1112
01:03:42.854 --> 01:03:45.303
better outcomes that we're wishing that we have for patients.

1113
01:03:46.694 --> 01:03:47.134
I think I'll,

1114
01:03:47.974 --> 01:03:51.934
as many others here have already shared with you, put forward the notion that

1115
01:03:52.094 --> 01:03:56.074
the pre-clinical models that we typically are using don't necessarily look like the

1116
01:03:56.124 --> 01:04:00.014
patients that we're treating. And that's really because in one

1117
01:04:00.034 --> 01:04:01.614
part, we're not accounting for aging.

1118
01:04:01.714 --> 01:04:05.624
So aging is associated with stromal remodeling, altered immune function, as we've

1119
01:04:05.654 --> 01:04:08.934
heard multiple times, and inflammaging, like we're talking about today and overall

1120
01:04:08.954 --> 01:04:09.584
in this session.

1121
01:04:10.454 --> 01:04:12.994
And this is very relevant in pancreas cancer.

1122
01:04:13.034 --> 01:04:15.874
We've seen the graphs for general cancers and other cancers before.

1123
01:04:15.934 --> 01:04:19.134
But in my mind, PDAC is one of the prototypic

1124
01:04:19.254 --> 01:04:23.014
age-associated malignancies. The average age of diagnosis is 71 years

1125
01:04:23.074 --> 01:04:26.974
old, with over 90% of patients being diagnosed at 55 or

1126
01:04:27.034 --> 01:04:30.814
older. And not just an incidence problem, but as we saw in breast

1127
01:04:30.874 --> 01:04:33.054
cancer, this is also an outcomes problem.

1128
01:04:33.114 --> 01:04:37.014
So if you look at patients with advanced or metastatic pancreas cancer,

1129
01:04:37.574 --> 01:04:41.214
the older patients do worse. And when I was a trainee in fellowship,

1130
01:04:41.434 --> 01:04:42.694
in med-onc fellowship,

1131
01:04:43.614 --> 01:04:43.754
my

1132
01:04:44.654 --> 01:04:46.053
naive thought was, well, they're older.

1133
01:04:46.074 --> 01:04:48.894
They're not able to get the chemotherapy that the younger patients could.

1134
01:04:48.934 --> 01:04:51.334
They can't get the Whipple surgery if we're talking about that.

1135
01:04:51.814 --> 01:04:55.134
This was a really nice study done in 2020 that controlled for those types of

1136
01:04:55.194 --> 01:04:59.054
things. So time on therapy, lines of therapy, ability

1137
01:04:59.114 --> 01:05:01.504
to go to surgery, and outcomes after surgery.

1138
01:05:02.114 --> 01:05:05.694
Controlling for all that, the older patients still do more poorly than younger

1139
01:05:05.754 --> 01:05:06.274
patients.

1140
01:05:07.714 --> 01:05:11.594
So when I was thinking about what to do in the lab about this and how can we model

1141
01:05:11.654 --> 01:05:15.234
this? And much like Dr. McAllister, we were thinking about, we need to account for

1142
01:05:15.274 --> 01:05:17.934
host aging to maybe model this a little better.

1143
01:05:18.674 --> 01:05:21.694
And we've used, again, implantable models.

1144
01:05:21.794 --> 01:05:25.254
So we use orthotopic injections of pancreas cancer models

1145
01:05:25.294 --> 01:05:27.954
to look at the tumor microenvironment and the effects.

1146
01:05:28.014 --> 01:05:31.434
And I'll use predominantly this cell line called KPC, which

1147
01:05:31.494 --> 01:05:35.294
recapitulates the major molecular and genetic alterations seen

1148
01:05:35.334 --> 01:05:39.284
in pancreas cancer patients. So P53 alterations, KRAS

1149
01:05:39.454 --> 01:05:43.344
mutations. But we've done this in multiple lines as well, different

1150
01:05:43.374 --> 01:05:45.534
models with pretty similar results.

1151
01:05:45.554 --> 01:05:48.234
So again, if we take young mice or aged mice.

1152
01:05:48.874 --> 01:05:52.474
Here it's over 12 months. We've done it 12, 15, 18.

1153
01:05:52.574 --> 01:05:56.484
Again, very consistent overall. What we find, in contrast to some other tumor types

1154
01:05:56.494 --> 01:06:00.134
like breast cancer or melanoma, is that primary tumors actually grow

1155
01:06:00.434 --> 01:06:04.034
more quickly in the older animals compared to the younger

1156
01:06:04.134 --> 01:06:08.054
animals. And in our first publication, we

1157
01:06:08.194 --> 01:06:10.764
looked at a lot of the signaling changes that happen in interactions with

1158
01:06:10.834 --> 01:06:14.714
fibroblasts. But as we were thinking about how do we transform outcomes here, and

1159
01:06:14.794 --> 01:06:18.414
what can we do about this lack of immunotherapy responsiveness in this disease?

1160
01:06:18.894 --> 01:06:21.824
We wanted to get a little more into the immune microenvironment and the immune

1161
01:06:21.894 --> 01:06:25.754
changes that are happening in the aged versus the young models.

1162
01:06:25.794 --> 01:06:29.014
So here I just wanted to show you, again, we get these larger tumors in the

