1166
01:06:40.014 --> 01:06:41.914
Now, this is what we see in our patients.

1167
01:06:41.974 --> 01:06:43.654
Like we told you, you have immune-excluded tumors.

1168
01:06:43.714 --> 01:06:47.074
So we are maybe modeling a little closer to what we see in the clinic.

1169
01:06:48.114 --> 01:06:51.754
Now, we again use a different model, and just as you can clone out different things

1170
01:06:51.774 --> 01:06:55.034
and get different behaviors, as Dr. McAllister really nicely showed in her talk.

1171
01:06:55.514 --> 01:06:58.794
The Stanger lab at Penn has a series of models called the

1172
01:06:58.814 --> 01:07:02.694
