1183
01:07:40.510 --> 01:07:44.100
We wanted to also take a look, well, what is the effectiveness of

1184
01:07:44.150 --> 01:07:48.050
this immune infiltrate in young versus aged animals, and how is it

1185
01:07:48.130 --> 01:07:49.930
impacting tumor growth and spread?

1186
01:07:50.530 --> 01:07:54.250
So we did a simple experiment where we just depleted T cells and broadly

1187
01:07:54.350 --> 01:07:58.150
CD4s and CD8s. I won't show you the breakdowns because it was very similar overall,

1188
01:07:58.210 --> 01:08:02.190
and took a look at what happened to the tumor size and other

1189
01:08:02.250 --> 01:08:04.130
metrics of tumor growth in these animals.

1190
01:08:04.890 --> 01:08:08.730
So here I'll show you that in young mice, maybe not surprisingly, if you take

1191
01:08:08.790 --> 01:08:10.950
away their T cells, these tumors get larger.

1192
01:08:11.390 --> 01:08:15.190
So clearly there was some sort of tumor control going on with what was

1193
01:08:15.270 --> 01:08:18.750
there in the tumor. But in the aged animals, there's no difference in tumor

1194
01:08:18.870 --> 01:08:22.830
growth with depletion of T cells. Again, that told me maybe

1195
01:08:22.910 --> 01:08:25.800
one of two things, probably one of a thousand things if you're realistic with

1196
01:08:25.830 --> 01:08:29.730
